description:
Tiny House Nation on FYITM follows renovation experts and hosts John Weisbarth and Zack Giffin as they travel across America to show off ingenious small spaces and the inventive people who live in them. Along the way, they also help families design and construct their own mini-dream homes in spaces no larger than 300 square feet. From a micro-apartment in New York City to a caboose car-turned-home in Montana to a micro-sized mobile home for road tripping, this series celebrates the exploding movement of tiny homes. Episode 1 172 Sq Ft Dream Castle
Released Jul 09, 2014
A young Tennessee couple is moving into a Tiny House with a toddler in tow. So our hosts John and Zack have to design a 172 sq. foot space that includes a pink castle, full kitchen, and master bedroom with privacy. But the toughest part? Building a home fit for a princess without making her parents feel like they're on a never-ending carousel ride.
